==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mastax
<hw>Mas"tax</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/
mouth, jaws.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The pharynx of
a rotifer. It usually contains four horny pieces. The two central ones
form the incus, against which the mallei, or lateral ones, work so as to
crush the food.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The lore of a bird.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Masted</ent>⟦br⟧
